  "output": "## Performance Analysis: Simplifii-OS\n\nHere are the 13 issues found, prioritized by impact:\n\n---\n\n### 1. CRITICAL — Sequential Awaits (N+1 Pattern)\n\n**4 locations** where async operations block in series instead of running in parallel.\n\n**`MasterDashboard.js:204-206`** — Archive migration:\n```javascript\n// BEFORE (serial — 100 saves = 50s)\nfor (const a of needs) {\n  try { await saveGhostAsset({ ...a, courseId: fallback }); } catch { /* ignore */ }\n}\n\n// AFTER (parallel — 100 saves = ~500ms)\nawait Promise.all(needs.map(a =>\n  saveGhostAsset({ ...a, courseId: fallback }).catch(() => {})\n));\n```\n\n**`MasterDashboard.js:306-309`** — Multi-course ingestion:\n```javascript\n// AFTER\nawait Promise.all(codes.map(code =>\n  handleSprintCreation({ ...data, unitCode: code, sourceFiles: groups[code] })\n));\n```\n\n**`UniversalOnboarding.js:259-264`** — PDF processing:\n```javascript\n// AFTER\nconst texts = await Promise.all(\n  files.map(f => processDocumentWithGCP(f, 'mock_jwt_token_xyz123'))\n);\ntexts.forEach(text => {\n  next = mergeExtractionData(next, { ...extractDeepCourseData(text), rawText: text });\n});\n```\n\n**`MasterDashboard.js:484-495`** — Grounding file ingestion: same pattern, same fix.\n\n---\n\n### 2. HIGH — Uncancelled setTimeout (Memory Leak)\n\n**`MasterDashboard.js:510`** — Bare `setTimeout` with no cleanup:\n```javascript\n// BEFORE\nsetTimeout(() => setIngestStatus(''), 6000);  // leaks if component unmounts\n\n// AFTER — move into useEffect\nuseEffect(() => {\n  if (!ingestStatus) return;\n  const id = setTimeout(() => setIngestStatus(''), 6000);\n  return () => clearTimeout(id);\n}, [ingestStatus]);\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. MEDIUM — Unmemoized Filter on Every Render\n\n**`MasterDashboard.js:1223-1224`** — IIFE inside JSX re-filters large array on every render:\n```javascript\n// BEFORE\n{(() => {\n  const courseAssets = globalGhostAssets.filter(a => a.courseId === activeCourseId);\n  // ...\n})()}\n\n// AFTER — hoist above return\nconst courseAssets = useMemo(\n  () => globalGhostAssets.filter(a => a.courseId === activeCourseId),\n  [globalGhostAssets, activeCourseId]\n);\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. MEDIUM — Class Names Recomputed Every Render\n\n**`MasterDashboard.js:688-689`**:\n```javascript\n// BEFORE\nconst leftSidebarClass = isZenMode ? 'w-0 opacity-0 px-0' : isLeftCollapsed ? 'w-16 px-2' : 'w-72 p-5';\n\n// AFTER\nconst leftSidebarClass = useMemo(\n  () => isZenMode ? 'w-0 opacity-0 px-0' : isLeftCollapsed ? 'w-16 px-2' : 'w-72 p-5',\n  [isZenMode, isLeftCollapsed]\n);\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. MEDIUM — Handlers Missing `useCallback`\n\n**`MasterDashboard.js:235-240`** — New function reference every render breaks memoized children:\n```javascript\n// AFTER\nconst handleAddGhostAsset = useCallback((asset) => {\n  const tagged = { ...asset, courseId: asset.courseId || activeCourseId };\n  saveGhostAsset(tagged).then(() =>\n    setGlobalGhostAssets(prev => [...prev, tagged])\n  );\n}, [activeCourseId]);\n```\n\n**`UniversalOnboarding.js:210-214`**:\n```javascript\nconst baseFromProfile = useCallback(() => ({\n  unitCode: profile.courseName,\n  level: profile.level,\n  theme: 'General'\n}), [profile.courseName, profile.level]);\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. LOW — Two Text Scans in BriefService\n\n**`BriefService.js:224-253`** — Two separate `matchAll` loops over the same text string. Combine into a single scan or deduplicate once at the end rather than per-loop.\n\n---\n\n### Summary\n\n| Priority | Issue | File | Estimated Gain |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| CRITICAL | Serial awaits in PDF/asset loops | MasterDashboard, Onboarding | 10–50x faster ingestion |\n| HIGH | `setTimeout` not cleared | MasterDashboard:510 | Prevents state updates on unmounted component |\n| MEDIUM | IIFE filter in JSX | MasterDashboard:1223 | Avoids O(n) per render |\n| MEDIUM | Sidebar class recompute | MasterDashboard:688 | Minor render savings |\n| MEDIUM | Missing `useCallback` on handlers | MasterDashboard, Onboarding | Prevents child re-renders |\n| LOW | Dual text scan | BriefService:224 | Minor CPU savings |\n\n**Start with the serial awaits** — they're the only issues with user-visible latency impact (PDF ingestion currently blocks sequentially for every file).\n",
